#supported_archs     noarch

description         Test::Mojibake - check your source for encoding misbehavior

long_description    Many modern text editors automatically save files using \
                    UTF-8 codification, however, perl interpreter does not \
                    expects it by default. Whereas this does not represent \
                    a big deal on (most) backend-oriented programs, Web \
                    framework (Catalyst, Mojolicious) based applications \
                    will suffer of so-called Mojibake (lit. \"unintelligible \
                    sequence of characters\").

